Student Information System (SIS) - Login & 2FA Portal by Team Villegas

A secure, web-based student portal featuring user registration, email/password login, and 2-Factor Authentication (2FA) via email verification.

üöÄ Key Features

Secure Sign Up: Captures student details (Name, ID, Age, Address, Birthdate) and securely creates an account.

Duplicate ID Check: Prevents multiple accounts from using the same Student ID number.

Data Storage: User profile data is stored in Cloud Firestore (NoSQL database).

2-Factor Authentication: Verifies user identity via a real SMS code sent to their registered phone number using Firebase Phone Auth.

Forgot Password: Allows users to reset their password via email link.

Responsive Design: Fully rectangular, grid-based layout that adapts to mobile devices.

üõ†Ô∏è Tech Stack

Frontend: HTML5, CSS3 (Inter Font), JavaScript (ES6 Modules)

Backend (BaaS): Firebase Authentication, Cloud Firestore

Hosting: Firebase Hosting (or Local Live Server for testing)

üìñ Usage Tutorial

1. Prerequisites

You do not need XAMPP, PHP, or MySQL running. This is a client-side app.

A modern web browser (Chrome, Edge, Firefox).

Internet connection (required for Firebase).

VS Code with "Live Server" extension (recommended for local testing).

2. Setup & Installation

Clone or download this repository.

Open the folder in VS Code.

Right click login.html and select "Open with Live Server".

3. How to Use

Sign Up:

Go to the Sign Up page.

Fill in your details.

Important: Enter a valid email address. This will be used for 2FA email verification.

Click Sign Up. You will be redirected to Login.

Log In:

Enter your registered Email and Password.

Click Sign In.

Magic Link Verification Usage in Firebase:

Step 1: You enter your Email AND Password.

Step 2: Firebase checks if the password is correct.

Step 3: If the password is correct, it sends the Magic Link to your email, if not in inbox CHECK SPAM FOLDER.

Step 4: You click the link in your email -> You get redirected to the Dashboard.


‚ö†Ô∏è Important Dev Notes from Deancv

FIREBASE SMS IS PAID AND CANT BE USED HERE, INSTEAD IM USING AN EMAIL VERIFICATION.
Firebase does NOT support "Email OTP" (sending a 123456 code to email) natively.

To achieve "2FA for every login" using Firebase's free tier is actually the Time-based One-Time Password (TOTP) feature (like Google Authenticator), but that requires an app.

Recommended Workaround (The "Magic Link" flow) will be implemented.